## ЁЯФ╣ SAN vs NAS (SAN рдФрд░ NAS рдореЗрдВ рдЕрдВрддрд░)

| Feature          | SAN                          | NAS                          |
|------------------|-------------------------------|-------------------------------|
| Network Type     | Block-level                   | File-level                    |
| Speed            | Faster                        | Slower                        |
| Use Case         | Databases, high-speed apps    | File sharing, backups         |
| Protocol         | Fibre Channel, iSCSI          | NFS, SMB                      |

---

## ЁЯФ╕ Summary (рд╕рд╛рд░рд╛рдВрд╢)

- SAN is used for fast, block-level storage access.  
- Best for large enterprise apps, databases, and virtualization.  
- Expensive but powerful.

